cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with image and video matting, which is a problem in computer vision. The use of sparse coding and non-parametric probabilistic segmentation suggests that this paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a graph model for video matting, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of dictionaries and closed-form solutions suggests that this paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
